title: Jamaican Gospel
description:
I'm Jamaican, might as well let everyone have a taste of our style of Gospel.
First we have a group called The Grace Thrillers and Glacier Robinson.
If you listen closely you can Understand. The Music is great and different in a good way. I recommend Survivor by G Robinson.

Now for Dancehall Gospel. to tell you the truth, if you ain't Jamaican,
you understand most words, except, and i'm going out on the limb with this: Naa Bow (translate: Not Going To Bow).

But the rhythms alone will get ya dancing and jumping all over the place (atleast it did for me lol) ENJOY and Comment. I really wanna see your feedback
